\\caption{Simplified View of Portion of Internet}
\\label{fig:1.6}
\\end{figure}

\\subsection{1.6 An Example Configuration}
To give some feel for the scope of concerns of this book, Figure~\\ref{fig:networking} illustrates some of the typical communications and network elements in use today. At the center of the figure is an IP backbone network, which could represent a portion of the Internet or an enterprise IP network. Typically, the backbone consists of high-performance routers, called \\emph{core routers}, interconnected with high-volume optical links. The optical links make use of what is known as wavelength division multiplexing (WDM), such that each link has multiple logical channels occupying different portions of the optical bandwidth.

