\\section{3.6 / KEY TERMS, REVIEW QUESTIONS, AND PROBLEMS} 129

\\begin{enumerate}
    \\item How many radians are there in a complete circle of 360 degrees?
    \\item What is the relationship between the wavelength and frequency of a sine wave?
    \\item Define fundamental frequency.
    \\item What is the relationship between a signal's spectrum and its bandwidth?
    \\item What is attenuation?
    \\item Define \\textit{channel capacity}.
    \\item What key factors affect channel capacity?
\\end{enumerate}

\\section*{Problems}

\\begin{enumerate}
    \\item a. For multipoint configuration, only one device at a time can transmit. Why?
    \\item b. There are two methods of enforcing the rule that only one device can transmit. In the centralized method, one station is in control and can either transmit or allow a specified other station to transmit. In the decentralized method, the stations jointly cooperate in taking turns. What do you see as the advantages and disadvantages of the two methods?
    \\item The period of a signal is $10^6$ ms. What is its frequency in megahertz?
    \\item A sine wave is shifted left by a 1/8 cycle at time 0.
    \\item a. Express its phase shift in degrees.
    \\item b. Express its phase shift in radians.
    \\item Sound may be modeled as sinusoidal functions. Compare the relative frequency and wavelength of musical notes. Use 330 m/s as the speed of sound and the following frequencies for the musical scale.
    \\begin{center}
        \\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|}
            \\hline
            \\textbf{Note} & C & D & E & F & G & A & B & C \\\\
            \\hline
            \\textbf{Frequency} & 264 & 297 & 330 & 352 & 396 & 440 & 495 & 528 \\\\
            \\hline
        \\end{tabular}
    \\end{center}
    \\item If the solid curve in Figure 3.17 represents $\\sin(2\\pi t)$, what does the dotted curve represent? That is, the dotted curve can be written in the form $A \\sin(2\\pi ft + \\phi)$; what are $A$, $f$, and $\\phi$?
    \\item Decompose the signal $(1 + 0.1 \\cos 5t) \\cos 100t$ into a linear combination of sinusoidal functions, and find the amplitude, frequency, and phase of each component. Hint: Use the identity for $\\cos a \\cos b$.
    \\item Find the wavelength of a 600-THz green light ray in air.
    \\item Consider two periodic functions $f_1(t)$ and $f_2(t)$, with periods $T_1$ and $T_2$, respectively. Is it always the case that the function $f(t) = f_1(t) + f_2(t)$ is periodic? If so, demonstrate this fact. If not, under what conditions is $f(t)$ periodic?
\\end{enumerate}

