\\begin{itemize}
    \\item Repeaters are used instead of amplifiers, so there is no cumulative noise.
    \\item As we shall see, time division multiplexing (TDM) is used for digital signals instead of the frequency division multiplexing (FDM) used for analog signals. With TDM, there is no intermodulation noise, whereas we have seen that this is a concern for FDM.
    \\item The conversion to digital signaling allows the use of the more efficient digital switching techniques.
\\end{itemize}

