The transmitted data may have a format something like Figure 8.6b. The data are organized into \\textbf{frames}. Each frame contains a cycle of time slots. In each frame, one or more slots are dedicated to each data source. The sequence of slots dedicated to one source, from frame to frame, is called a \\textbf{channel}. The slot length equals the transmitter buffer length, typically a bit or a byte (character).

