\\begin{itemize}
    \\item \\textbf{Sequence Control:} Contains a 4-bit fragment number subfield, used for fragmentation and reassembly, and a 12-bit sequence number used to number frames sent between a given transmitter and receiver.
    \\item \\textbf{QoS Control:} Contains information relating to the IEEE 802.11 quality of service (QoS) facility. A discussion of this facility is beyond our scope.
    \\item \\textbf{High Throughput Control:} This field contains control bits related to the operation of 802.11n, 802.11ac, and 802.11ad. A discussion of this field is beyond our scope.
    \\item \\textbf{Frame Body:} Contains an MSDU or a fragment of an MSDU. The MSDU is a LLC PDU or MAC control information.
    \\item \\textbf{Frame Check Sequence:} A 32-bit cyclic redundancy check.
\\end{itemize}

We now look at the three MAC frame types.

