The $h_{ij}$ are complex numbers $x + jz$ that represent both the amplitude attenuation ($x$) over the channel and the path dependent phase shift ($z$), and the $n_i$ are additive noise components. The receiver measures the channel gains based on training fields containing known patterns in the packet preamble and can estimate the transmitted signal with the following equation:
\\[
\\begin{bmatrix}
\\hat{c}_1 \\\\
\\hat{c}_2 \\\\
\\hat{c}_3
\\end{bmatrix}
=
\\mathbf{H}^{-1}
\\begin{bmatrix}
y_1 \\\\
y_2 \\\\
y_3 \\\\
y_4
\\end{bmatrix}
\\]

