OFDM has several advantages. First, frequency selective fading only affects some subcarriers and not the whole signal. If the data stream is protected by a forward error-correcting code, this type of fading is easily handled. More important, OFDM overcomes intersymbol interference (ISI) in a multipath environment. As discussed in Chapter 3, ISI has a greater impact at higher bit rates, because the

