    \\item \\textbf{Network Access Provider (NAP):} A business entity that provides WiMAX radio access infrastructure to one or more WiMAX Network Service Providers.
    \\item \\textbf{Connectivity Service Network (CSN):} A set of network functions that provide IP connectivity services to WiMAX subscribers. These functions include Internet access, authentication, and admission control based on user profiles.
