\\section{Constrained Shortest-Path First Algorithm}

The CSPF algorithm is an enhanced version of the shortest-path first (SPF) algorithm used in OSPF. CSPF computes paths taking into account multiple constraints. When computing paths for LSPs, CSPF considers the topology of the network, the attributes of the individual links between LSRs, and the attributes of existing LSPs. CSPF attempts to satisfy the requirements for a new LSP while minimizing congestion by balancing the network load.

Figure~\\ref{fig:cspf_flowchart} suggests the context in which CSPF is used. In setting up a new LSP, CSPF operates on the basis of three inputs:

